subSubSection.paragraph:
Hemispermatophore (Fig: 19-e): Lamelliform (TL: 3.6; LL: 1.2; LW: 
0.8 mm
); lamella straight, as wide as capsule; hook short, basal, composed of a single lobe. Capsule entally with median lobe well sclerotized.

Variation (
Table 2
): The presence of sexual dimorphism in this species is noticeable in the development of the vesicular gland on males, whereas in females this gland is inconspicuous or absent. Additionally the body size is larger on females (
24–27 mm
) than on males (usually 
20–21 mm
). Full morphometric variation is given in tables 13 and 14. Setae variation is given in tables 9–12.
